          "reviewBody": "My daughter studying here since 5 years. But right after corona they have turned in to a business rather than a school of education.price  Hike in fees hike in book sets but there is no hike in there standards of studies no substitute for the subjects if a teacher is absent. Even when the things comes on to visual and performing arts students spent their periods either watching senior kids performances or as a free period. Due to their extra curriculums I chose this school. My Last year was full of complaints but I guess in this year they are doing the same. They are busy in snaching money from our pockets rather than looking for our kids bright future.",
          "publisher": {
